</div>
<p id="zL0mul">But the V60 lacks some of the features that are increasingly common on “flagship” Android devices in 2020. There’s no fluid 90Hz or 120Hz display; LG instead sticks with a traditional, no-frills 60Hz panel. Its bezels are plain to see and thicker than what you’d find on a Samsung or OnePlus. As other high-end devices move up to 12GB of RAM (and beyond), LG is being slightly conservative with 8GB of memory. And despite continued refinement, the Dual Screen accessory never really unlocks its full potential: the big selling point is still that basic, core ability to run different apps side by side at the same time. But LG’s hallmarks — a good camera, blissful headphone audio, and top-notch performance — are still represented in the V60. Pricing is a little scattered, with the phone itself costing $800 (T-Mobile) or around $900 with the Dual Screen on Verizon and AT&amp;T. Either way, you come in under the S20’s $999 sticker price.</p>
<p id="TyHgfy">The V60 just <em>does so much</em> (doubly so if you get it with the Dual Screen) that, in a vacuum, it’s hard not to be impressed. The battery life is astounding, and it’s an excellent choice for the type of person who will use every trick this phone has in its arsenal. If that’s not you, there’s ample reason to look at Samsung or OnePlus instead. </p>
<div class="c-wide-block">  <figure class="e-image">
  <span class="e-image__inner">
    
    <span class="e-image__image " data-original="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19901232/cwelch_200414_3974_0003.jpg">
      
        <picture class="c-picture" data-cid="site/picture_element-1587260636_1971_61539" data-cdata='{"asset_id":19901232,"ratio":"*"}'>
  


  <source srcset="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/acjF_cMoMCPnMDcigJaxj05I8PA=/0x0:2040x1360/320x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19901232/cwelch_200414_3974_0003.jpg 320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/TEAD8nwDaZkbNZ5Xp9rwaWt_5DY=/0x0:2040x1360/520x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19901232/cwelch_200414_3974_0003.jpg 520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/cG4ikcPFWsD61ffbwNUDoX7vxzA=/0x0:2040x1360/720x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19901232/cwelch_200414_3974_0003.jpg 720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/N2TGFKit9MBLY3x29fTzQslUvvQ=/0x0:2040x1360/920x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19901232/cwelch_200414_3974_0003.jpg 920w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/E2X1vDIUR9ajPiUo8-fjlkdFyV0=/0x0:2040x1360/1120x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19901232/cwelch_200414_3974_0003.jpg 1120w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/xVFfaEfyn0NVrDwk-q7wvlBUDxE=/0x0:2040x1360/1320x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19901232/cwelch_200414_3974_0003.jpg 1320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/f-iZ_sHwerWVi-FatguZk6l2iG4=/0x0:2040x1360/1520x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19901232/cwelch_200414_3974_0003.jpg 1520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/cc7278VwFKSUphp6OuROsN_yNuc=/0x0:2040x1360/1720x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19901232/cwelch_200414_3974_0003.jpg 1720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/1eRmQL-jMUT8DfvSBzPehsEL1rc=/0x0:2040x1360/1920x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):format(webp):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19901232/cwelch_200414_3974_0003.jpg 1920w" sizes="90vw" type="image/webp">


<img srcset="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/puAiZsxpg0qv4Wg-9Dm35HV9Nfg=/0x0:2040x1360/320x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19901232/cwelch_200414_3974_0003.jpg 320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/jDCDGn_0oT7XTYV5QdQadE6ppug=/0x0:2040x1360/520x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19901232/cwelch_200414_3974_0003.jpg 520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/dH94Cr3MgArZr8o8KyGTyoEJzoo=/0x0:2040x1360/720x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19901232/cwelch_200414_3974_0003.jpg 720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/JbQZ822_UqvPknECTiw2FeVgnRc=/0x0:2040x1360/920x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19901232/cwelch_200414_3974_0003.jpg 920w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/f_pgbFjeqLuLBmqXBdiv2LH34DE=/0x0:2040x1360/1120x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19901232/cwelch_200414_3974_0003.jpg 1120w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/99QY43m6aBV-Hb5pxHwUvd1Nd4M=/0x0:2040x1360/1320x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19901232/cwelch_200414_3974_0003.jpg 1320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/QGgMY2bno87jTg6rZkAqZXfYHLE=/0x0:2040x1360/1520x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19901232/cwelch_200414_3974_0003.jpg 1520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/RSlV1H6uQBhV5KwBFLjYQWdafwM=/0x0:2040x1360/1720x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19901232/cwelch_200414_3974_0003.jpg 1720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/meiip0-MBb_Mm5HEyJmsffocIho=/0x0:2040x1360/1920x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19901232/cwelch_200414_3974_0003.jpg 1920w" sizes="90vw" alt="" data-upload-width="2040" src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/9F991qnmMQBGN-wQkehpOJH486c=/0x0:2040x1360/1200x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19901232/cwelch_200414_3974_0003.jpg">

</source></picture>

      
    </span>
    
  </span>
  
</figure>

</div>
<p id="FldgE7">Fair warning, though: even people familiar with LG’s past efforts will be taken aback by the V60’s size. This is a big, honking phone. At 6.67 inches tall and 3.06 inches wide, it’s somehow even larger than the <a href="https://www.theverge.com/2020/2/27/21155012/samsung-galaxy-s20-ultra-review-5g-screen-camera-space-zoom-price">Galaxy S20 Ultra</a> and pays absolutely no mind to ergonomics. It’s <em>possible</em> to use the V60 with one hand, but doing so is an ill-advised exercise in finger gymnastics and grip adjustments. The chamfered aluminum rails offer a secure grasp on the phone, which has a flat 6.8-inch screen and sloped glass back. Volume toggles and a non-remappable Google Assistant shortcut button take up the left side, with the power button on the right. The V60 comes with 128GB of storage, but it supports microSD expansion. </p>
<p id="EvgrcP">At the bottom, you’ll find a speaker (which doubles up with the earpiece for stereo output), USB-C port, and a headphone jack, which still includes LG’s excellent 32-bit DAC for audiophile-grade music playback — if you’ve got the right headphones to get the most from it. LG gets my praise both for keeping the jack around and delivering a listening experience that can rival dedicated hi-fi audio players. Listening to hi-res tracks in Amazon Music HD with my Sennheiser headphones made me appreciate LG’s quest to preserve the headphone jack even when everyone else has moved on.</p>
