<img srcset="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/POf3RPNKFETefXujNFNPVh_npkA=/0x0:2040x1360/320x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19730011/cwelch_200218_3910_0015.jpg 320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Or0BVPYqZMyV8_b_HBpOPJo3uQo=/0x0:2040x1360/520x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19730011/cwelch_200218_3910_0015.jpg 520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/2ulnoqaHn6dol84_GKta6xb47Sk=/0x0:2040x1360/720x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19730011/cwelch_200218_3910_0015.jpg 720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/dyrVkXYSApL9905f_yB9C9JpylE=/0x0:2040x1360/920x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19730011/cwelch_200218_3910_0015.jpg 920w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/OYCwMunYvNY0jU9dH8Ebr4YZom4=/0x0:2040x1360/1120x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19730011/cwelch_200218_3910_0015.jpg 1120w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/SUSCJXks_fGKrq5R_ecgAVsDUtk=/0x0:2040x1360/1320x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19730011/cwelch_200218_3910_0015.jpg 1320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/-0TQ9_YaIi3ioGmQc_WVrQJtHKk=/0x0:2040x1360/1520x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19730011/cwelch_200218_3910_0015.jpg 1520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/zHeju598putDMiGOI7MBnwPzp30=/0x0:2040x1360/1720x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19730011/cwelch_200218_3910_0015.jpg 1720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/qXei3cZQb8y3naVY4kwKIsp93Z8=/0x0:2040x1360/1920x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19730011/cwelch_200218_3910_0015.jpg 1920w" sizes="90vw" alt="" data-upload-width="2040" src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/_1pBEQGHG6Rlq6RpLfXL4wfPzZg=/0x0:2040x1360/1200x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19730011/cwelch_200218_3910_0015.jpg">

</source></picture>

      
    </span>
    
  </span>
  
</figure>

</div>
<p id="uxBHKm">Throughout my review period, the Snapdragon 865 chipset has performed flawlessly, with the V60 chewing through any task I threw at it. Wi-Fi 6 is supported, and the V60 can pull down 5G data on T-Mobile and AT&amp;T, though only Verizon is selling a version that works with ultra-fast (but very limited) millimeter-wave 5G. </p>
<div><div id="aHnJ4A">
<div class="c-entry-sidebar">
  <h1 id="Jzkw0F">AGREE TO CONTINUE: LG V60</h1>
<p id="cNyI3a"><em>Every smart device now requires you to agree to a series of terms and conditions before you can use it — contracts that no one actually reads. It’s impossible for us to read and analyze every single one of these agreements. But we started counting exactly how many times you have to hit “agree” to use devices when we review them, since these are agreements most people don’t read and definitely can’t negotiate.</em></p>
<p id="BSbBg2">To use the LG V60 ThinQ 5G, you must agree to:</p>
<ul>
<li id="k16Yld">LG privacy agreement</li>
<li id="mUCcfD">Google terms of service (including privacy policy)</li>
<li id="wfu5ic">Google Play terms of service</li>
</ul>
<p id="8jdile">For contactless payments, you must agree to:</p>
<ul><li id="v0NH5w">
<a href="https://www.lg.com/us/lg-pay/LG-Pay-Privacy-Policy.pdf" data-analytics-viewport="related-story" data-analytics-link="related-story">LG Pay privacy policy</a> (.pdf link)</li></ul>
<p id="nTiSRa">Note that LG’s carrier partners — in this case Verizon, AT&amp;T, and T-Mobile — have their own privacy policies and will sometimes request location access or permission to store data on your device for their various services </p>
<p id="ML7MIH">In total, that’s three mandatory agreements and an optional one for LG Pay. </p>
</div>
</div></div>
<p id="7LQPjq">Like the G8x, the V60’s Dual Screen connects over USB-C. There’s a little magnetic adapter that attaches to the bottom of the case if you want to plug in for charging while it’s on, though fast wireless charging is the more convenient option in that scenario. The secondary screen is an exact match for the primary display, with the same resolution and even the notch cutout. (It’s literally the same panel part, which LG says helps cut costs and preserve color uniformity.)</p>
