_0011.jpg 1920w" sizes="90vw" type="image/webp">


<img srcset="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/tnVcdotf_ViaU9TwEvTt3_Cx1Ck=/0x0:2040x1360/320x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19730007/cwelch_200218_3910_0011.jpg 320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/H6V6YEMCQT1W4efqU2e_b-ArysA=/0x0:2040x1360/520x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19730007/cwelch_200218_3910_0011.jpg 520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/V7p9ROZFSK9gYNqdijaG2lcGJSM=/0x0:2040x1360/720x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19730007/cwelch_200218_3910_0011.jpg 720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/uKQfDCmrIyYZXhiM0xl69MPNYfA=/0x0:2040x1360/920x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19730007/cwelch_200218_3910_0011.jpg 920w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/HWxaf2qW18jfIYg_J2Tom4VXibY=/0x0:2040x1360/1120x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19730007/cwelch_200218_3910_0011.jpg 1120w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/K1gt44Mtv_rW2AmZssRbf2opjtY=/0x0:2040x1360/1320x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19730007/cwelch_200218_3910_0011.jpg 1320w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Q24q4jOIOmqjpHR_WCzB2iYX1wA=/0x0:2040x1360/1520x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19730007/cwelch_200218_3910_0011.jpg 1520w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/H6NHXJKEAR-Hv_-Sv8_K3cQjA1g=/0x0:2040x1360/1720x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19730007/cwelch_200218_3910_0011.jpg 1720w, https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/546ZKp7JNQt7IKgGnzHCamqbUuo=/0x0:2040x1360/1920x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19730007/cwelch_200218_3910_0011.jpg 1920w" sizes="90vw" alt="" data-upload-width="2040" src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/8ef6iuZmRhiMUpQwTzwrK6otPCU=/0x0:2040x1360/1200x0/filters:focal(0x0:2040x1360):no_upscale()/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/19730007/cwelch_200218_3910_0011.jpg">

</source></picture>

      
    </span>
    
  </span>
  
</figure>

</div>
<p id="5ACky1">And then there’s the bloatware. LG is not selling an unlocked version of the V60 in the US, so you’re at the mercy of Verizon, AT&amp;T, and T-Mobile — and it’s not pretty. After setting up the phone, you’ll find at least five or six games you don’t want and a handful of carrier apps that you can’t fully uninstall. The Verizon V60 constantly presented me with a “helpful” device health notification that encouraged me to restart the phone and clear its memory cache. These are unnecessary, annoying distractions that people really don’t need to worry about. </p>
<p id="kSfm0j">One of the most under-the-radar perks of the V60 is proper stylus support. If you buy a Wacom pen, you’ll get Galaxy Note-like pressure sensitivity for drawing. There’s an optional slide-in shortcuts bar where you can quickly start writing a new memo, annotate whatever’s on your screen, and access other tricks. LG doesn’t have its own stylus like Samsung’s S-Pen or a slot to carry one in, but what’s here is pretty useful and, again, speaks to the V60’s versatility. </p>
<p class="c-end-para" id="OCgYCS">It should say everything about the V60 being a jack-of-all-trades that I’m ending on stylus support. This phone gives you a <em>ton</em> for $800 — even if you go without the Dual Screen. It’s a blazing performer, battery life might be the best for any phone in 2020 so far, and it’s got terrific headphone audio. But I really wish LG had done more with the giant display. I can put up with the bezels just fine, but high-refresh screens are already becoming table stakes at this price in the Android world. If I’m sacrificing comfort and ergonomics, the display had better be incredible. And I’m willing to pay a couple extra hundred bucks for it. </p>
<p id="SBtdHM"><em>Photography by Chris Welch / The Verge</em></p>
